# Creating & dropping the table

Introduction to table
> A database is just a bunch of tables, that were data is store.
> Table holds data: A collection of related data held in a structed formate within a database.

# Data Types
1. Numeric Types
> INT
> DECIMAL
> FLOAT
> DOUBLE

2. STRING TYPES
> CHAR
> VARCHAR
> ENUM

3. DATE TYPES
> DATE
> TIMESTAMP
> TIME
> YEAR

# Syntax for creating a table
CREATE TABEL <table_name>
(
column_name datatype,
column_name datatypes
);

Example:
CREATE TABLE cats
(
name varchar(100),
age int
);

# To check the status of table:
  SHOW TABLES;
this query will retrive the tabla data.


To know the structure of the data:
  DESCRIBE cats;
OR
  SHOW COLUMNS FROM cats
# To Drop the table
DROP TABLE CATS; 

# To create a table:
CREATE TABLE pastries
(
name varchar(50),
qunatity int
);

# To drop table named pastries:-
DROP TABLE pastries
